{"id":"323350151_A_Self-Resetting_Spiking_Phase-Change_Neuron","abstract":"Neuromorphic, or brain-inspired, computing applications of phase-change devices have to date concentrated primarily on the implementation of phase-change synapses. However, the so-called accumulation mode of operation inherent in phase-change materials and devices can also be used to mimic the integrative properties of a biological neuron. Here we demonstrate, using physical modelling of nanoscale devices and SPICE modelling of associated circuits, that a single phase-change memory cell integrated into a comparator type circuit can deliver a basic hardware mimic of an integrate-and-fire spiking neuron with self-resetting capabilities. Such phase-change neurons, in combination with phase-change synapses, can potentially open a new route for the realisation of all-phase-change neuromorphic computing.","authors":["Rosie Cobley","Hasan Hayat","David Wright"],"meta":["February 2018Nanotechnology 29(19)","DOI:10.1088/1361-6528/aab177"],"references":["320807032_Calculating_with_light_using_a_chip-scale_all-optical_abacus","320079806_On-chip_photonic_synapse","317343983_Temporal_correlation_detection_using_computational_phase-change_memory","311445870_Neuromorphic_computing_using_non-volatile_memory","306248734_Large-scale_neuromorphic_computing_systems","266143176_A_Model_for_Multilevel_Phase-Change_Memories_Incorporating_Resistance_Drift_Effects","257973238_Physical_aspects_of_low_power_synapses_based_on_phase_change_memory_devices","252007647_Drift-Tolerant_Multilevel_PhaseChange_Memory","51484362_Neuromorphic_Silicon_Neuron_Circuits","51240876_Arithmetic_and_Biologically-Inspired_Computing_Using_Phase-Change_Materials","50363879_Low-Power_Switching_of_Phase-Change_Materials_with_Carbon_Nanotube_Electrodes","13434362_Synaptic_Modifications_in_Cultured_Hippocampal_Neurons_Dependence_on_Spike_Timing_Synaptic_Strength_and_Postsynaptic_Cell_Type","6413206_Brain_Oscillations_Control_Timing_of_Single-Ne